If the injection is tangential,

492
00:30:48,632 --> 00:30:52,122
that is as parallel as possible

493
00:30:52,122 --> 00:30:54,936
to the toroidal direction,

494
00:30:54,936 --> 00:30:57,094
we will start with mostly passing orbits,

495
00:30:57,094 --> 00:31:00,244
that is orbits,
as you can see in this movie,

496
00:31:00,244 --> 00:31:03,919
that are circulating around the tokamak,

497
00:31:03,919 --> 00:31:05,894
but of course there
will be some collisions,

498
00:31:05,896 --> 00:31:08,608
and the collisions scatter
the circulating particles

499
00:31:08,608 --> 00:31:11,645
into trapped orbits, as you can see,

500
00:31:12,169 --> 00:31:16,493
not only from the representation
in real space on the left,

501
00:31:16,493 --> 00:31:19,875
but also from the representation
in the velocity speeds on the right,

502
00:31:19,875 --> 00:31:25,906
where the ions are going from passing,

503
00:31:25,906 --> 00:31:29,318
to being trapped by collisional effects,

504
00:31:29,318 --> 00:31:34,144
this is a simulation in a realistic
tokamak environment.

505
00:31:34,537 --> 00:31:36,708
So these are the characters
of the orbits that we have

506
00:31:36,708 --> 00:31:41,821
for the fast, or energetic ions
that are injected from NBI.

507
00:31:42,512 --> 00:31:45,975
That's important not only for the heating

508
00:31:45,975 --> 00:31:50,482
and the possibility of driving
a non-inductive current in the plasma

509
00:31:50,482 --> 00:31:55,630
with these energetic particles,
but also for the potential interaction

510
00:31:55,630 --> 00:31:58,142
that these particles can have
with plasma instabilities

511
00:31:58,142 --> 00:32:01,554
as we will see in a lecture in the future.

512
00:32:02,161 --> 00:32:06,271
I would like now to discuss briefly

513
00:32:06,271 --> 00:32:09,280
some concrete examples of NBI system.

514
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:10,931
First of all a system that exists,

515
00:32:10,931 --> 00:32:12,226
and in fact has been operational

516
00:32:12,226 --> 00:32:14,547
for a number of years, that of JET.

517
00:32:15,179 --> 00:32:19,809
JET has different injectors, 2x8,

518
00:32:19,809 --> 00:32:22,602
both for radial and tangential injection,

519
00:32:22,602 --> 00:32:27,962
at either 80keV or 130keV of energy.

520
00:32:28,519 --> 00:32:34,036
This is sufficient for the beam to go into
the core of the JET plasma,

521
00:32:34,036 --> 00:32:37,560
and these energies, as we said before,

522
00:32:38,738 --> 00:32:40,828
don't require negative ion technology

523
00:32:40,828 --> 00:32:46,059
because the neutralization of
positive ions is sufficiently efficient.

524
00:32:46,782 --> 00:32:51,111
The JET system has up to
34MW of total power

525
00:32:51,111 --> 00:32:53,081
in its recent upgrades.

526
00:32:53,081 --> 00:32:55,299
You can see the size of the system here,

527
00:32:56,418 --> 00:33:00,222
which is almost the same
as that of the entire tokamak.

528
00:33:00,582 --> 00:33:03,051
We can look at some of the details.

529
00:33:03,488 --> 00:33:07,388
Here is the layout of the system,
with the one injector

530
00:33:07,388 --> 00:33:10,021
with eight ion sources,

531
00:33:11,613 --> 00:33:16,036
with insulators and seals
that you can see in the layout here,

532
00:33:16,036 --> 00:33:17,773
and you can see in the actual picture

533
00:33:17,773 --> 00:33:20,730
when the system was installed,
on the right.

