594
00:36:59,213 --> 00:37:02,072
As we mentioned,
the charge exchange process

595
00:37:02,616 --> 00:37:06,035
provides light, that carries information
about the ion temperature

596
00:37:06,035 --> 00:37:09,162
and about the ion ordered
velocity, as well.

597
00:37:09,162 --> 00:37:11,883
Now in order for that process to dominate,

598
00:37:11,883 --> 00:37:14,321
remember that we need
to have low energies,

599
00:37:15,505 --> 00:37:19,829
and therefore we inject in the beam,
we will be injecting in the beam in ITER

600
00:37:19,829 --> 00:37:24,703
at an energy of about 100keV
for diagnostic purposes,

601
00:37:24,703 --> 00:37:27,473
a beam that won't have, of course,
much of a power,

602
00:37:27,473 --> 00:37:29,401
of the order of 3MW.

603
00:37:30,034 --> 00:37:34,508
So here you see a layout
of the geometry of injection

604
00:37:34,508 --> 00:37:37,731
into the ITER tokamak, seen from the top.

605
00:37:37,731 --> 00:37:43,031
And you see a CAD drawing
of the three systems,

606
00:37:43,031 --> 00:37:45,297
the two heating and current drive systems

607
00:37:45,297 --> 00:37:50,817
and the diagnostic beam,
into the ITER system.

608
00:37:51,577 --> 00:37:53,672
Now the source itself,

609
00:37:53,672 --> 00:37:57,568
and the whole beam accelerating system

610
00:37:57,568 --> 00:38:00,880
and the neutralization for ITER
is a challenge,

611
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:05,978
and that's why it's still
the subject of significant R&D.

612
00:38:06,457 --> 00:38:11,028
There will be a very large
surface source,

613
00:38:11,028 --> 00:38:13,492
with a couple of square meters of surface

614
00:38:13,492 --> 00:38:16,602
which needs to produce
a very large current density,

615
00:38:16,602 --> 00:38:20,287
something like 300A/mÂ²,

616
00:38:20,287 --> 00:38:24,135
with a high degree of uniformity
across the surface.

617
00:38:25,310 --> 00:38:28,752
The concept used is so-called MaMuG,

618
00:38:28,752 --> 00:38:34,588
that extracts and accelerates the ions
produced from this source.

619
00:38:34,588 --> 00:38:36,941
Multi-Aperture Multi-Grid
Accelerator System,

620
00:38:36,941 --> 00:38:39,042
each step is 200 kV.

621
00:38:39,042 --> 00:38:42,262
For the source itself,
the technology,

622
00:38:42,262 --> 00:38:46,299
based on the radio frequency
production of a plasma

623
00:38:46,299 --> 00:38:49,948
is used, as opposed to arc discharges.

624
00:38:49,948 --> 00:38:54,723
The choice was based on
the reliability tests

625
00:38:54,723 --> 00:38:58,506
having been made in different devices,
and also on the need of having

626
00:38:58,506 --> 00:39:03,442
very low maintenance requirements

627
00:39:03,442 --> 00:39:07,687
for the system, once it's operational.

628
00:39:08,002 --> 00:39:12,117
I'll just highlight the fact that
the negative ions are produced

629
00:39:12,117 --> 00:39:18,049
on surfaces
that are covered with cesium,

630
00:39:18,646 --> 00:39:24,017
it has been deposited on them,
so low work function surfaces,

631
00:39:24,772 --> 00:39:28,062
and this is a surface production
of a plasma.

632
00:39:28,062 --> 00:39:33,197
We're talking about, of course,
the source for the neutral beam,

633
00:39:33,197 --> 00:39:35,250
as opposed to the volume production

634
00:39:35,250 --> 00:39:39,755
we have seen in,
for example, the JET system,

635
00:39:39,755 --> 00:39:44,017
which is based on arc discharges.

636
00:39:44,753 --> 00:39:47,671
So this is the source,
that's the acceleration stage,

637
00:39:48,073 --> 00:39:52,421
the neutralizer has quite a large volume,
the Residual Ion Dump, the calorimeter,

638
00:39:52,421 --> 00:39:54,651
so all the elements we have seen for JET,

639
00:39:54,651 --> 00:39:57,472
and of course there will be a valve
and a set of bellows

640
00:39:57,472 --> 00:40:01,685
to connect the whole system
to the tokamak.

641
00:40:02,476 --> 00:40:06,731
We are now ready to discuss,
in a simple way,

642
00:40:06,731 --> 00:40:10,517
the possible advantages and disadvantages
of the NBI heating system.

643
00:40:11,266 --> 00:40:12,977
We have seen that the interaction between

644
00:40:12,977 --> 00:40:16,453
the beam and the plasma is fairly simple.

645
00:40:16,453 --> 00:40:19,749
There are three essential processes,

646
00:40:19,749 --> 00:40:21,658
of which in fact two dominate:

647
00:40:22,603 --> 00:40:25,463
charge exchange and ionization by ions,

648
00:40:25,463 --> 00:40:27,271
depending on the beam energy.

649
00:40:27,822 --> 00:40:29,926
The beam has an advantage
that can be used

650
00:40:29,926 --> 00:40:32,475
to drive current non-inductively,

651
00:40:32,475 --> 00:40:36,344
if it's directed in a tangential way.

652
00:40:37,384 --> 00:40:41,692
It also has the advantage that
it can provide fuelling of the plasma,

653
00:40:41,692 --> 00:40:44,716
and in fact provide fuelling on the plasma
in the core of the plasma,

654
00:40:44,716 --> 00:40:46,962
if the penetration depth is sufficient.

655
00:40:47,598 --> 00:40:50,402
And in fact these advantages
are the reason why

656
00:40:50,402 --> 00:40:54,694
in present experiments I can say that
the NBI represents the workhorse,

657
00:40:54,694 --> 00:40:57,274
particularly for
high-performance operation.

658
00:40:58,291 --> 00:41:01,215
On the other hand,
there may be some cons.

659
00:41:02,024 --> 00:41:06,760
The position of the power
is not that localized,

660
00:41:06,760 --> 00:41:10,040
so it may be a little bit difficult
to determine exactly

661
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:14,079
a localization for the heating
or the current drive.

662
00:41:15,194 --> 00:41:19,595
The beam implies a relatively large
beam duct, as we have seen,

663
00:41:19,595 --> 00:41:22,639
so there would be a relatively large
opening in the chamber

664
00:41:22,639 --> 00:41:24,219
to make the beam pass through.

665
00:41:24,219 --> 00:41:29,330
That means that we have to be careful 
about the leaking of neutrons

666
00:41:29,330 --> 00:41:32,656
out of the thermonuclear region,

667
00:41:33,204 --> 00:41:34,789
and also we're losing some surface

668
00:41:34,789 --> 00:41:37,635
that we could use for the blanket
to breed tritium.

669
00:41:38,691 --> 00:41:44,005
The present technology of the beams
has relatively low electrical efficiency,

670
00:41:44,005 --> 00:41:47,541
which of course in
the future reactor is a problem,

671
00:41:48,769 --> 00:41:53,640
and also, even if we go
for negative ions at large energies,

672
00:41:54,822 --> 00:41:59,397
at large energies we do have relatively
small neutralization efficiency,

673
00:41:59,397 --> 00:42:01,731
not much better than 60%.

674
00:42:02,149 --> 00:42:05,487
For these two potential problems,
nevertheless,

675
00:42:05,487 --> 00:42:09,974
there are significant R&D activities
going on to improve the situation.

676
00:42:09,974 --> 00:42:12,417
We'll just give you one example of them.

677
00:42:13,364 --> 00:42:16,986
This example is provided by
the so-called SIPHORE concept,

678
00:42:16,986 --> 00:42:21,539
in which a new technology
for the plasma source [is developed]

679
00:42:22,688 --> 00:42:26,402
This technology is based on
the resonant antenna

680
00:42:26,402 --> 00:42:28,476
that drives the plasma,

681
00:42:28,999 --> 00:42:30,884
using helicon waves.

682
00:42:30,884 --> 00:42:34,584
In fact, helicon waves
are a kind of waves

683
00:42:34,945 --> 00:42:38,506
that you have seen in a previous course,

684
00:42:38,833 --> 00:42:41,141
focused on the physics of plasma waves.

685
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:45,560
We can refer to them also
as <i>whistler</i> waves.

686
00:42:46,472 --> 00:42:49,667
Incidentally, this reminds you
of the importance of plasma waves

687
00:42:50,281 --> 00:42:52,778
in many, many applications.

688
00:42:53,465 --> 00:42:56,805
Once the plasma is producing that source,

689
00:43:00,189 --> 00:43:04,034
and ions are extracted
from that source region,

690
00:43:04,034 --> 00:43:05,744
of course they need to be neutralized,

691
00:43:05,744 --> 00:43:08,165
and we have seen that
the neutralization efficiency is

692
00:43:08,165 --> 00:43:09,992
one of the problems we're facing.

693
00:43:10,323 --> 00:43:14,918
But the idea in this proposal
is to use light

694
00:43:15,525 --> 00:43:20,202
to increase efficiency
by providing photoneutralization.

695
00:43:20,700 --> 00:43:23,239
Photoneutralization acts
by photodetachment,

696
00:43:24,289 --> 00:43:28,223
so we have a negative ion,
in this case the example of hydrogen,

697
00:43:28,223 --> 00:43:30,733
on which we inject a photon,

698
00:43:31,065 --> 00:43:35,301
and that provides neutralization
of that negative ion,

699
00:43:35,301 --> 00:43:37,045
and of course the emission
of an electron,

700
00:43:37,045 --> 00:43:39,997
which can then be deflected
by the electron magnet later on.

701
00:43:40,445 --> 00:43:42,962
This is a concept
that's been investigated,

702
00:43:42,962 --> 00:43:46,642
and may potentially provide
both higher electrical efficiency

703
00:43:46,642 --> 00:43:48,483
for the plasma production in the source,

704
00:43:48,483 --> 00:43:52,522
and higher neutralization efficiency
using laser light.

705
00:43:52,939 --> 00:43:55,620
In summary, we have seen
that additional heating is required

706
00:43:55,620 --> 00:43:57,227
for thermonuclear reactors.

707
00:43:57,227 --> 00:43:59,850
By additional heating we mean
heating that comes

708
00:43:59,850 --> 00:44:03,304
on top of the Ohmic heating,
which is a consequence

709
00:44:03,304 --> 00:44:05,832
of electrical current
flowing into the plasma.

710
00:44:05,832 --> 00:44:08,808
The first system
we have investigated today

711
00:44:08,808 --> 00:44:10,849
was the neutral beam injector.

712
00:44:11,436 --> 00:44:15,925
A neutral beam provides a solution
that has a number of advantages,

713
00:44:15,925 --> 00:44:19,233
but some drawbacks,
although some of the drawbacks

714
00:44:19,233 --> 00:44:22,419
can be overcome,
and that's why we are doing

715
00:44:22,419 --> 00:44:26,397
significant amounts of research
and development on this issue.

716
00:44:26,871 --> 00:44:29,757
In the next two modules, we'll investigate
how we can heat the plasma

717
00:44:29,757 --> 00:44:31,938
using plasma waves
at different frequencies.
